### .NET version

Issue can be reproduced in any .NET version. 

### Did it work in .NET Framework?

No

### Did it work in any of the earlier releases of .NET Core or .NET 5+?

No

### Issue description

I'm creating a custom Form with rounded corners. 

I'm using the below given code to get rounded corners. 

**Note** : It is just a sample code to reproduce my problem. 

```
public partial class Form1 : Form
{
    [DllImport("Gdi32.dll", EntryPoint = "CreateRoundRectRgn")]
    private static extern IntPtr CreateRoundRectRgn
(
    int nLeftRect,     // x-coordinate of upper-left corner
    int nTopRect,      // y-coordinate of upper-left corner
    int nRightRect,    // x-coordinate of lower-right corner
    int nBottomRect,   // y-coordinate of lower-right corner
    int nWidthEllipse, // width of ellipse
    int nHeightEllipse // height of ellipse
);

    [DllImport("user32.dll", CharSet = CharSet.Auto, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Winapi)]
    internal static extern int SetWindowRgn(IntPtr hWnd, IntPtr hRgn, bool bRedraw);

    [DllImport("gdi32")]
    internal static extern bool DeleteObject(IntPtr hObject);
    public Form1()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        this.BackColor = Color.DarkGray;
        this.FormBorderStyle = FormBorderStyle.None;
        IntPtr hRgn = CreateRoundRectRgn(0, 0, Width, Height, 10, 10);

        if (hRgn != IntPtr.Zero)
        {
            SetWindowRgn(this.Handle, hRgn, true);
            DeleteObject(hRgn);
        }
    }
}
```


I can get the rounded corners. But, the corners doesn't seem smooth. Is there any way to fix this. Any help would be appreciated. Image attached below.

